<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/StringUTF8>
        a       <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class>;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy>
                <http://qudt.org/$$QUDT_VERSION$$/schema/datatype>;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "String UTF8 Type";
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf>
                <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/TextStringType> , <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/StringType>;
        <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description>
                "\n  String UTF-8 Type is a string data type that specifies the properties of string data structures which encode strings using the UTF-8 encoding. \n  UTF-8 includes ASCII, otherwise referred to as IA-5 (International Alphabet 5, as standardized by International Organization for Standardization [ISO]) as the first 128 values. \n  The Internet Engineering Task Force (IETF) requires all Internet protocols to identify the encoding used for character data with UTF-8 as at least one supported encoding. \n  The Internet Mail Consortium (IMC) recommends that all e-mail programs must be able to display and create mail using UTF-8.\n  ";
        <http://www.linkedmodel.org/schema/vaem#isElaboratedIn>
                <http://qudt.org/$$QUDT_VERSION$$/schema/shacl/datatype> .

