        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy>
                <http://qudt.org/$$QUDT_VERSION$$/schema/datatype>;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "is heterogeneous";
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range>
                <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .

<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/oleDBName>
        a       <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty> , <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty>;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy>
                <http://qudt.org/$$QUDT_VERSION$$/schema/datatype>;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "OLE DB name";
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range>
                <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string>;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf>
                <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/id>;
        <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description>
                "OLE DB (Object Linking and Embedding, Database, sometimes written as OLEDB or OLE-DB), an API designed by Microsoft, allows accessing data from a variety of sources in a uniform manner. The API provides a set of interfaces implemented using the Component Object Model (COM); it is otherwise unrelated to OLE. " , "\n  <p>OLE DB (Object Linking and Embedding, Database, sometimes written as OLEDB or OLE-DB), an API designed by Microsoft, allows accessing data from a variety of sources in a uniform manner. \n  The API provides a set of interfaces implemented using the Component Object Model (COM); it is otherwise unrelated to OLE.\n  </p>"^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#HTML>;
        <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/informativeReference>
                "http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms714931(v=vs.85).aspx"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> , "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OLE_DB"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI>;
        <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasInfluencedBy>
                <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OLE_DB> , <http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms714931(v=vs.85).aspx> .

<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#gYearMonth>
        a       <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#Datatype> .

<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/FixedIntervalTimeSeriesArray>
        a       <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class>;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy>
                <http://qudt.org/$$QUDT_VERSION$$/schema/datatype>;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "Fixed Interval Time Series Array Type";
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf>
                <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/TimeSeriesArray>;
        <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description>
                "\n  <p>A <em>Fixed Interval Time Series Array Type</em> is a data type that specifies the properties of arrays that hold time series data.\n  For example, data that has been sampled over uniformly spaced time intervals.\n  A time series is a sequence of data points, measured typically at successive times, spaced at uniform or non-uniform time intervals.\n  </p>"^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#HTML> .

